  "eprint": {
    "title": "Fast hybrid Karatsuba multiplier for Type II pentanomials",
    "authors": [
      {
        "name": "Yin Li",
        "email": "yunfeiyangli@gmail",
        "affiliation": ""
      },
      {
        "name": "Yu Zhang",
        "email": "",
        "affiliation": ""
      },
      {
        "name": "Wei He",
        "email": "",
        "affiliation": ""
      }
    ],
    "abstract": "We continue the study of Mastrovito form of Karatsuba multipliers under the shifted polynomial basis (SPB), recently introduced by Li et al. (IEEE TC (2017)).\nA Mastrovito-Karatsuba (MK) multiplier utilizes the Karatsuba algorithm (KA) to optimize polynomial multiplication and the Mastrovito approach to combine it with the modular reduction. The authors developed a MK multiplier for all trinomials, which obtain a better space and time trade-off compared with previous non-recursive Karatsuba counterparts.\nBased on this work, we make two types of contributions in our paper.\n\nFORMULATION. We derive a new modular reduction formulation for constructing Mastrovito matrix associated with Type II pentanomial. This formula can also be applied to other\nspecial type of pentanomials, e.g. Type I pentanomial and Type C.1 pentanomial.\nThrough related formulations, we demonstrate that Type I pentanomial is less efficient than Type II one because of a more complicated modular reduction under the same SPB;\nconversely, Type C.1 pentanomial is as good as Type II pentanomial under an alternative generalized polynomial basis (GPB).\n\n\nEXTENSION. We introduce a new MK multiplier for Type II pentanomial. It is shown that our proposal is only one $T_X$ slower than the fastest bit-parallel multipliers for Type II pentanomial, but its space complexity is roughly 3/4 of those schemes, where $T_X$ is the delay of one 2-input XOR gate. To the best of our knowledge, it is the first time for hybrid multiplier to achieve such a time delay bound.",
    "keywords": [
      "Karatsuba algorithm",
      "hybrid multiplier",
      "Mastrovito",
      "Shifted polynomial basis",
      "Type II pentanomial"
    ],
    "category": "Implementation",
    "publication_info": "Preprint. MINOR revision.",
    "last_updated": "2020-07-28",
